  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two diagrams of three fixed point charges. From left to right, each diagram shows charge negative Q sub 0, positive Q sub 0, and positive Q sub 3. The first diagram is labeled “Initial Positions of Three Point charges.” In it, charge positive Q sub 0 is a distance D to the right of charge negative Q sub 0, and charge positive Q sub 3 is far to the right of charge positive Q sub 0. The second figure is labeled “Final Positions of Three Point Charges.” In it, charge positive Q sub 0 is a distance D to the right of charge negative Q sub 0, and charge positive Q sub 3 is a distance D to the right of charge positive Q sub 0.\" src=\"/images/05b6cb6c607504df9ad2c9ee883e7bbb.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two point charges of opposite sign, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"negative Q sub 0\"><math alttext=\"negative Q sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mpadded></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q sub 0\"><math alttext=\"positive Q sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mpadded></math></span></span>, are fixed in place a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"D\"><math alttext=\"D\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>D</mi></math></span></span> apart from each other, as shown in the figure, while a third point charge with positive charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q sub 3\"><math alttext=\"positive Q sub 3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></mpadded></math></span></span> is initially located a long distance away on the line joining <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"negative Q sub 0\"><math alttext=\"negative Q sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mpadded></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q sub 0\"><math alttext=\"positive Q sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mpadded></math></span></span>. An external force moves point charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q sub 3\"><math alttext=\"positive Q sub 3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></mpadded></math></span></span> along the line until it is in its final position a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"D\"><math alttext=\"D\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>D</mi></math></span></span> to the right of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q sub 0\"><math alttext=\"positive Q sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mpadded></math></span></span>. Which of the following claims is true during the time that point charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q sub 3\"><math alttext=\"positive Q sub 3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></mpadded></math></span></span> is being moved from its initial position to its final position?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i4",
